==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Purchasable
<hw>Pur"chas*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being bought, purchased, or obtained for a consideration; hence, venal;
corrupt.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Money being the counterbalance to all things
<qex>purchasable</qex> by it, as much as you take off from the value of
money, so much you add to the price of things exchanged.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Purchase</ent>⟦br⟧
